    "summary": "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">The aim of the course is to acquaint students with the basics of mathematics and the </span><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">basic concepts necessary for Data Science and economic thinking: differential and integral calculus of </span><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">multivariate real functions and probability. In addition to all this, the aim is to develop problem-solving </span><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">skills and to strengthen students' commitment to precise, demanding economic work through practical </span><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">tasks. The course, as a mathematics subject for thought development, contributes to the development of </span><span style=\"font-size:0.875rem;\">rigorous rational thinking and is part of basic economic and finance education.</span></p><br /><p></p>",
